24. Use Case Definition
Based on the identified actors, the core use cases of the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System are defined as follows:
Report Incident – Allows employees to submit cybersecurity incident reports.
Classify Incident Severity – Automatically or manually assigns severity levels to reported incidents.
Track Incident Status – Enables users to view the current  status and progress of incidents.
Initiate Response Workflow – Allows SOC analysts to follow guided response steps.
Update Incident Status – Enables SOC analysts to update incident lifecycle stages.
Manage Users and Roles – Allows administrators to manage system users and permissions.
User Authentication – Verifies user identity and controls access based on roles.
Monitor Incident Dashboard – Provides real-time visualization of incidents and severity levels.
Generate Reports and Audit Logs – Produces compliance, audit, and performance reports.
These use cases collectively describe the primary functionalities required for effective cybersecurity incident reporting, monitoring, and response management within the organization.
